background: A university research lab can make two types of diabetes medicine using limited imported material and mRNA, with different per-dose requirements for each medicine.

parameters.definition: Units of imported material to make one dose of medicine A
Units of mRNA to make one dose of medicine A
Units of imported material to make one dose of medicine B
Units of mRNA to make one dose of medicine B
Total units of imported material available
Maximum doses of medicine A that can be made
Number of people treated by one dose of medicine A
Number of people treated by one dose of medicine B

constraints.description: Each dose of medicine A must be a non-negative quantity
Number of doses of medicine B must be non-negative
constraints.code: # Since DosesOfMedicineB is already defined as non-negative by default in Gurobi when the variable type is CONTINUOUS, no additional code is required.

constraints.description: Total imported material used for producing medicine A and B should not exceed the TotalMaterial available
constraints.code:
# TotalMaterial constraint: Total imported material used for producing medicine A and B
model.addConstr(MaterialA * DosesOfMedicineA + MaterialB * DosesOfMedicineB <= TotalMaterial, name="total_material_constraint")

constraints.description: Total mRNA used in producing medicine A and B should not exceed the total available units of mRNA
constraints.code:
# Constraint: Total mRNA used for medicine A and B should not exceed the total available units of mRNA
model.addConstr(MrnaA * DosesOfMedicineA + MrnaB * DosesOfMedicineB <= TotalMrna, "total_mrna_usage")

constraints.description: The lab can make at most MaxDosesA doses of medicine A
constraints.code:
# Add constraint for the maximum doses of medicine A
model.addConstr(DosesOfMedicineA <= MaxDosesA, name="max_doses_of_medicine_A")

constraints.description: The number of doses of medicine B must be greater than the number of doses of medicine A
The total units of imported material used cannot exceed the total units available
constraints.code: model.addConstr(DosesOfMedicineA * MaterialA + DosesOfMedicineB * MaterialB <= TotalMaterial, name="material_usage")

constraints.description: The total units of mRNA used cannot exceed the total units available
constraints.code:
# Constraint: The total units of mRNA used cannot exceed the total units available
model.addConstr(DosesOfMedicineA * MrnaA + DosesOfMedicineB * MrnaB <= TotalMrna, name="total_mRNA_usage")

constraints.description: The number of doses of medicine A produced cannot exceed the maximum number allowed
constraints.code:
# Add constraint for the maximum number of doses of medicine A
model.addConstr(DosesOfMedicineA <= MaxDosesA, name="max_doses_A")

variables.definition: Number of doses of medicine A produced
Number of doses of medicine B produced

objective.description: Maximize the total number of people treated with doses of medicine A and B
objective.code:
# Set objective
model.setObjective(DosesOfMedicineA * PeopleA + DosesOfMedicineB * PeopleB, gp.GRB.MAXIMIZE)
